  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2294795988" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2294795988" />
    <a title="Alex" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/39328440-alex"><img alt="Alex" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1478414998p2/39328440.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2294795988?book_show_action=true">May 11, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alex" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alex" href="/user/show/39328440-alex">Alex</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2294795988" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4557050781656016366">Fortunately this book is short. However, not short enough. The premises of the book are interesting enough to make one read at least half of it wondering what is going to happen next. But after that everything is just painful. The whole story smells staged and faked - the story, the dialgoues, the monologues, everything is fake in this book. Fake and boring. <br/>The story starts announcing some big family drama, and some skeletons in the closet to be discovered, however, the whole drama is described</span>
  <span id="freeText4557050781656016366" style="display:none">Fortunately this book is short. However, not short enough. The premises of the book are interesting enough to make one read at least half of it wondering what is going to happen next. But after that everything is just painful. The whole story smells staged and faked - the story, the dialgoues, the monologues, everything is fake in this book. Fake and boring. <br />The story starts announcing some big family drama, and some skeletons in the closet to be discovered, however, the whole drama is described so emotionlessly, with lots of dialogues it makes it totally artificial. <br />There are 5 persons (+ Declan =6) which take turn in soliloquing about their lives and dramas and stuff. BORING !!!! Only Declan throws up and has diarrhea almost on every page. He doesnt speak that much.<br />"Nora Webster", another book from Toibin I read, had also some boring element in it, however it succeded in catching my attention. Probably because it had some main story and not so many as "The Blacwater Lightship" has - the story of the grandmother with the mother, the mother with the daughter, the grandmother and mother with the daughter, the gay stories, the AIDS stuff, the coping with AIDS and gay-being in the catholic institution and family and so on; ah, the story of Helen and Hugh, their children and the relationship with Helens mother. And this in only 295 pages !!!! </span>
  <a data-text-id="4557050781656016366" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


