        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer406185287" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14748091787902601505">A beautifully written family drama set in Ireland in the early 1990s, which was the beginning of the Celtic Tiger period. The pain and misunderstanding between three generations of women are so well presented. The tension builds up gradually. The ending is open. There is also an embedded gay love story. <br/><br/>Colm Tóibín is indeed a master of literature.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


