        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2904986833" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9756491030936669928">Why can’t we all just get along? <br/><br/>I gravitate towards dark fiction, but something about this one really got to me. Maybe because there is nothing darker than not being in contact with your immediate family. And then being thrust together to comfort (?) someone as they’re dying. Colm Tóibín is one of my favorite writers AND human beings. I wouldn’t have been so gutted by this if he weren’t such an amazing author. It’s not like I wasn’t warned by the quote on the front: “Beautifully crafted...spare</span>
  <span id="freeText9756491030936669928" style="display:none">Why can’t we all just get along? <br /><br />I gravitate towards dark fiction, but something about this one really got to me. Maybe because there is nothing darker than not being in contact with your immediate family. And then being thrust together to comfort (?) someone as they’re dying. Colm Tóibín is one of my favorite writers AND human beings. I wouldn’t have been so gutted by this if he weren’t such an amazing author. It’s not like I wasn’t warned by the quote on the front: “Beautifully crafted...spare and devastating.” Exactly.<br /><br />Written in 1999. Shortlisted for the Booker Prize.<br /><br />Bought at Three Lives on a lovely trip to New York City in June 2018. </span>
